{"title_page": "Lena Raine", "text_new": "{{Short description|American composer}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| image            = Lena Raine at 2018 GDC IGF Awards.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Raine at the 2018 GDC IGF Awards\n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_date       = February 29, 1984 (age 36)\n| birth_place      = \n| alias            = Lena Chappelle\n| genre            = \n| occupation       = Composer, producer\n| years_active     = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| label            = {{Flatlist|\n*Materia Collective\n*Ship To Shore PhonoCo\n*Local Action\n}}\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|http://lena.fyi/}}\n}}\n\n'''Lena Raine''' (born February 29, 1984) is an American composer. She is best known for her work on the soundtrack of ''[[Celeste (video game)|Celeste]]''. In 2019, she released her debut album, ''Oneknowing''.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/yw88gk/lena-raine-oneknowing-celeste-interview|title=Lena Raine's Digital Ambience Can Make You Panic or Help You Relax|last=Goldner|first=Cayce Clifford,Sam|date=2019-03-29|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n* ''Hackmud Original Soundtrack'' (2016)\n* ''Celeste Original Soundtrack'' (2018)\n* ''ESCISM: ESC Original Soundtrack'' (2018)\n* ''Oneknowing'' (2019)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* ''Chicory: An Afternoon in Luncheon'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techraptor.net/originals/crowdfunding-spotlight-chicory-colorful-tale|title=Crowdfunding Spotlight - Chicory: A Colorful Tale|website=TechRaptor|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n* ''Celeste: Farewell Original Soundtrack'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2019/09/09/celeste-has-set-off-on-its-final-farewell-update/|title=Celeste has set off on its final Farewell update|last=Clayton|first=Natalie|date=2019-09-09|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://lena.fyi/}}\n\n{{Composer-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Female composers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Video game composers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American composer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| image            = Lena Raine at 2018 GDC IGF Awards.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Raine at the 2018 GDC IGF Awards\n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_date       = February 29, 1984 (age 36)\n| birth_place      = \n| alias            = Lena Chappelle\n| genre            = \n| occupation       = Composer, producer\n| years_active     = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| label            = {{Flatlist|\n*Materia Collective\n*Ship To Shore PhonoCo\n*Local Action\n}}\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|http://lena.fyi/}}\n}}\n'''Lena Raine''' (born February 29, 1984) is an American composer. She is best known for her work on the soundtrack of ''[[Celeste (video game)|Celeste]]''. In 2019, she released her debut album, ''Oneknowing''.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/yw88gk/lena-raine-oneknowing-celeste-interview|title=Lena Raine's Digital Ambience Can Make You Panic or Help You Relax|last=Goldner|first=Cayce Clifford,Sam|date=2019-03-29|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n* ''Hackmud Original Soundtrack'' (2016)\n* ''Celeste Original Soundtrack'' (2018)\n* ''ESCISM: ESC Original Soundtrack'' (2018)\n* ''Oneknowing'' (2019)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* ''Chicory: An Afternoon in Luncheon'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techraptor.net/originals/crowdfunding-spotlight-chicory-colorful-tale|title=Crowdfunding Spotlight - Chicory: A Colorful Tale|website=TechRaptor|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n* ''Celeste: Farewell Original Soundtrack'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2019/09/09/celeste-has-s