{"title_page": "Wilhelm Olss\u00f8n", "text_new": "[[File:Wilhelm Olss\u00f8n.jpg|thumb|upright|Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n]]  \n'''Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n''' (5 April 1844 - 3 November 1915) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]]  military officer and politician. \n<ref>{{cite web|url=   http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=18103\n|title=  Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n|publisher=    Norsk samfunnsvitenskapelig datatjeneste AS |accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOlss\u00f8n was born in [[Horten]] in [[Vestfold]], Norway.  He was the son of Edvard Olss\u00f8n  (1820-1867) and Leonore Rebecca Bredal (1820-1910. He received a military education at the [[Norwegian Military Academy]] (1866) and [[Norwegian Military College]] (1870). He received  additional education at the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] in [[Stockholm]] (1872-1874).<ref>{{cite web|url=    https://nbl.snl.no/Wilhelm_Olss%25C3%25B8n|title =  Wilhelm Olss\u00f8n, Offiser, Politiker|publisher =   Norsk biografisk leksikon\n|author=Paul Thyness|accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe was appointed major general in 1896. In 1898, he was commander at Oscarsborg, 1899 inspector general for coastal artillery. In 1907, he became lieutenant-general. He retired from military service in 1912 as Commanding General. He served as Minister of Defence 1893\u20131894, 1895\u20131898, 1905\u20131907, and member of the Council of State Division in [[Stockholm]] 1894\u20131895.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=18103|title=  Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n\n|publisher=    Norsk samfunnsvitenskapelig datatjeneste AS |accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{succession box|before=O. Hansen|after=[[Einar Wilhelm Anton Martin Krohn]]|title=Commanding General in Norway|years=1910\u20131912}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Olsson, Wilhelm}}\n[[Category:1844 births]]\n[[Category:1915 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Horten]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Norway]]\n[[Category:Norwegian Army generals]]\n[[Category:Norwegian Military Academy alumni]]\n[[Category:KTH Royal Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Norwegian people of Swedish descent]]\n\n\n{{Norway-politician-1840s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Wilhelm Olss\u00f8n.jpg|thumb|upright|Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n]]  \n'''Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n''' (5 April 1844 - 3 November 1915) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]]  military officer and politician. \n<ref>{{cite web|url=   http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=18103\n|title=  Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n|publisher=    Norsk samfunnsvitenskapelig datatjeneste AS |accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOlss\u00f8n was born in [[Horten]] in [[Vestfold]], Norway.  He was the son of Edvard Olss\u00f8n  (1820-1867) and Leonore Rebecca Bredal (1820-1910. He received a military education at the [[Norwegian Military Academy]] (1866) and [[Norwegian Military College]] (1870). He received  additional education at the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] in [[Stockholm]] (1872-1874).<ref>{{cite web|url=    https://nbl.snl.no/Wilhelm_Olss%25C3%25B8n|title =  Wilhelm Olss\u00f8n, Offiser, Politiker|publisher =   Norsk biografisk leksikon\n|author=Paul Thyness|accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe was appointed major general in 1896. In 1898, he was commander at Oscarsborg, 1899 inspector general for coastal artillery. In 1907, he became lieutenant-general. He retired from military service in 1912 as Commanding General. He served as Minister of Defence 1893-1894, 1895-1898, 1905\u20131907, and member of the Council of State Division in [[Stockholm]] 1894-1895.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=18103|title=  Christian Wilhelm Engel Bredal Olss\u00f8n\n|publisher=    Norsk samfunnsvitenskapelig datatjeneste AS |accessdate= June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{succession box|before=O. Hansen|after=[[Einar Wilhelm Anton Martin Krohn]]|title=Commanding General in Norway|years=1910\u20131912}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Olsson, Wilhelm}}\n[[Category:1844 births]]\n[[Category:1915 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Horten]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Norway]]\n[[Category:Norwegian Army generals]]\n[[Category:Norwegian Military Academy alumni]]\n[[Category:KTH Royal Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Norwegian people of Swedish descent]]\n\n\n{{Norway-politician-1840s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1893-1894 \u2192 1893\u20131894 (3)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilhelm_Olss%C3%B8n"}
